The paper deals with cryptographic paradigms and one-way functions, which are typically studied in the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves the study of the degree of ambiguity of one-way functions, which falls under the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of associative one-way functions and their properties also suggests a connection to the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper involves mathematical proofs and analysis, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
